      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "LAND OF NOD (2) settled in the second half of the field and ran over the top to win in impressive fashion on the Scarpside circuit here most recently. He showed plenty of ability there and looks suited by the rise in trip again today. Can continue to improve and land the knockout blow again. SAIGON DANCER (3) lobbed midfield on resumption at Northam and flew right by his rivals to win by 2.7L in dominant fashion. Chris Parnham now hops on board from a good barrier and she too looks better suited getting out in trip. Wouldn't surprise to see her repeat the dose. FRIAR'S LEGACY (1) has missed in both runs this campaign by 0.8L and is right on the cusp. Back to an easier race today and he gets plenty of favours from the barrier draw. Can get back to winning ways now. DOMINANT FORCE (5) just missed in a similar race first-up and has to be included. ROSENTREA (4) is not out of this on her latest efforts.",
